                                <h2>How Alternative Finance Can Support The Rise of Unicorns </h2>
                            </div>
                            <br/>
                            <p>
                                With COVID restrictions and lockdowns continuing to wreak havoc on traditional industries all over the world, many technology
                                startups are thriving in a forced digital environment. The recent
                                <strong>$39 billion acquisition of AfterPay by Square</strong> is a clear success story for an ASX
                                listed company, but there are many other Aussie companies that are turning into unicorns
                                through multi-million venture capital rounds in 2021:
                                <strong>Octopus Deploy ($223M), SafetyCulture ($99M), Canva ($92M) and Athena Home Loans ($90M).</strong>
                                <br/> 
                            </p>
                            <p>As Aussie tech startups continue to thrive, investors are turning to alternative assets,
                                such as venture capital and equity crowdfunding, in the search for growth.</p>

                            <ul class="p-rich_text_list p-rich_text_list__bullet" data-stringify-type="unordered-list" data-indent="0">
